{%- comment -%}
  App Block (target: section) — merchants drag this into their product
  template via the theme editor for pixel-precise placement (e.g. right above
  the title, or below the price), unlike the App Embed's site-wide heuristic
  placement on cards/search/etc.

  `product` is already in Liquid scope here because the block is rendered
  inside the product template's main section, so no metafield or setting is
  needed to know which product this is. The container is just a marked
  anchor point — badge-renderer.js (shared with the App Embed) finds it via
  data-product-handle and fills it in.
{%- endcomment -%}

<div
  class="product-badges-anchor"
  data-product-badges-target="product-detail-page"
  data-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
  data-product-handle="{{ product.handle }}"
></div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:product_badge.name",
  "target": "section",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
